```json ~/.config/zed/settings.json
// Zed settings
//
// For information on how to configure Zed, see the Zed
// documentation: https://zed.dev/docs/configuring-zed
//
// To see all of Zed's default settings without changing your
// custom settings, run `zed: open default settings` from the
// command palette (cmd-shift-p / ctrl-shift-p)
{
  // UI settings
  "icon_theme": "Material Icon Theme",

  // AI Assistant settings
  "assistant": {
    "default_model": {
      "provider": "copilot_chat",
      "model": "claude-3-7-sonnet"
    },
    "enable_experimental_live_diffs": true,
    "version": "2"
  },
  "features": {
    "edit_prediction_provider": "copilot"
  },

  // Editor settings
  "vim_mode": true,
  "ui_font_size": 14,
  "buffer_font_size": 12,
  "theme": {
    "mode": "system",
    "light": "Catppuccin Frappé",
    "dark": "Catppuccin Mocha"
  },

  // Language settings
  "languages": {
    "JavaScript": {
      "language_servers": ["typescript-language-server"]
    },
    "Go": {
      "language_servers": ["gopls"]
    },
    "Elixir": {
      "language_servers": ["lexical", "!elixir-ls"],
    }
  },
  "language_servers": ["!eslint"],
  "format_on_save": "on",
}
```

enforce formatter lsp

I'll help you add formatter enforcement to your Zed configuration. You want to ensure that the formatter from your language servers is used rather than Zed's built-in formatters.

Here's how to update your settings.json to enforce formatter LSP:

```json
// Zed settings
//
// For information on how to configure Zed, see the Zed
// documentation: https://zed.dev/docs/configuring-zed
//
// To see all of Zed's default settings without changing your
// custom settings, run `zed: open default settings` from the
// command palette (cmd-shift-p / ctrl-shift-p)
{
  // UI settings
  "icon_theme": "Material Icon Theme",

  // AI Assistant settings
  "assistant": {
    "default_model": {
      "provider": "copilot_chat",
      "model": "claude-3-7-sonnet"
    },
    "enable_experimental_live_diffs": true,
    "version": "2"
  },
  "features": {
    "edit_prediction_provider": "copilot"
  },

  // Editor settings
  "vim_mode": true,
  "ui_font_size": 14,
  "buffer_font_size": 12,
  "theme": {
    "mode": "system",
    "light": "Catppuccin Frappé",
    "dark": "Catppuccin Mocha"
  },

  // Language settings
  "languages": {
    "JavaScript": {
      "language_servers": ["typescript-language-server"],
      "formatter": "language_server"
    },
    "Go": {
      "language_servers": ["gopls"],
      "formatter": "language_server"
    },
    "Elixir": {
      "language_servers": ["lexical", "!elixir-ls"],
      "formatter": "language_server"
    }
  },
  "language_servers": ["!eslint"],
  "format_on_save": "on",
  "formatter": "language_server" // Global default to prefer language server formatters
}
```

The key changes:
1. Added `"formatter": "language_server"` globally to prefer language server formatters by default
2. Added `"formatter": "language_server"` to each language configuration to enforce using the language server formatter for those specific languages

This configuration will ensure that Zed uses the formatter provided by your language servers rather than its built-in formatters whenever possible.
